item.dc:creator: @Rune_Hacker1 Rune Hacker
item.description:
@Rune_Hacker1 wrote:

But using click mouse will get you banned EXTREMELY fast, so never use it runescape scripting, but be glad to use it in other scripts. In runescape, we use Mouse(x,y,12,2, True) instead of clickmouse. It is in srl. So best thing to do it look for the color of the cammy teliport or something(bitmap preferaly, but thats advanced), tell use the mouse i typed, and then add a bunch of random waits or soemthing to prevent ban like Wait(500+random(100+random(75)+random(150))), this makes the wait more random and prevents it being detected. SRL is great for runescape because is it virtualy undetectable if used right. If you need any help or have any questions, feel free to message me.

item.title: Auto Camelot Teleporter
item.dc:creator: @dudeofthed dudeofthed
item.description:
@dudeofthed wrote:

Woah, instead of adding all those ClickMouse functions just put a repeat function. And yes it is very bad as Rune Hacker said. And i wouldn’t think that there would be any randoms when teleporting Rune Hacker. Try to use MoveMouseSmooth(x,y); with a few bitmaps.

For example:[code]program CamelotTeleporter;
{.include SRL\SRL.scar}

var
BitmapOfMagicBook, BitmapOfTeleportSign, BitmapOfCamelotLocation, x, y: Integer;
procedure LoadBMPS;
begin
BitmapOfMagicBook:=’’+ //Bitmap Code and name goes here
‘’; //Same as above…

BitmapOfTeleportSign:=’’+ //Bitmap Code and name goes here
‘’; //Same as above…

BitmapOfCamelotLocation:=’’+ //Bitmap Code and name goes here
‘’; //Same as above…
end;
procedure MoveToBook;
begin
if(FindBitmap(BitmapOfMagicBook,x,y)) then
Wait(1000)
MoveMouseSmooth(x,y);
Wait(900)
ClickMouse(x,y,True);
Wait(1200)
end;

procedure StartTeleport;
begin
if(FindBitmap(BitmapOfTeleportSign,x,y)) then
Wait(700)
MoveMouseSmooth(x,y);
Wait(1900)
if(FindBitmap(BitmapOfCamelotLocation,x,y)) then
Wait(780)
ClickMouse(x,y,True);
end else
if(FindBitmap(BitmapOfTeleportSign)) then
MoveMouseSmooth(x,y);
Wait(1500)
if(FindBitmap(BitmapOfCamelotLocation,x,y)) then
ClickMouse(x,y,True);
end;

begin
repeat
LoadBMPS;
MoveToBook;
StartTeleport;
Until(IsFKeyDown(9))
end.[/code]

But that code won’t work, it is just an example.

item.dc:creator: @Rune_Hacker1 Rune Hacker
item.description:
@Rune_Hacker1 wrote:

Sorry, but that is very bad. It will get you banned VERY fast, not reliable, no anti-ban, no antirandoms, no failsafes.

You should learn a lot more before trying a script. Sorry if i sound mean.

Add srl in the script, add antirandoms, make is so you can add as a const how many teliports you want to do, and stuff like that. You can learn all about stuff like this at http://www.srl-forums.com/forum/tutorial-beginners-f176.html

Read through the begginer tutorials there and you will learn a lot and it will help you a lot in furture scripts. There is also a camelot teliporter there in the free script section that you can look at i belive.
